idence and access permissions are up to date before the audit begins.\r\n\r\nCheck_2 \r\n\r\nVerify that all required documents are current and accessible.\r\n\r\nPerform a brief pre-audit walkthrough to confirm readiness.	Act_1 \r\n\r\nAnalyze external audit feedback and integrate lessons learned into the audit readiness framework.\r\n\r\nUpdate policies, procedures, and documentation templates based on auditor recommendations.\r\n\r\nAutomate document collection and evidence mapping for future audits using GRC or compliance tools.\r\n\r\nSchedule post-audit review to strengthen weak areas before the next cycle.\r\n\r\nAct_2 \r\n\r\nRecord audit feedback and make minor improvements to the readiness checklist.\r\n\r\nPlan refresher sessions for teams to improve next-year readiness.		[]	\N	[]	\N	00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001	d180076a-533c-4c0a-8f7b-ffa0fbe8eb2b	murali@hepl.com	\N	CADP
