ults in employee records.	Do_1 (Strong Execution)\r\n\r\nImplement screening for all new hires before granting access to any organizational systems or sensitive data.\r\n\r\nCoordinate between HR, Legal, and Security teams to ensure screening completion.\r\n\r\nMaintain a tracking system or HR database to record verification results and clearance levels.\r\n\r\nApply conditional offers ∩┐╜ employment is confirmed only after successful screening.\r\n\r\nConduct periodic rescreening for employees in sensitive or critical positions.\r\n\r\nRestrict access to background reports to authorized HR/security personnel only.\r\n\r\nProvide HR staff with training on data privacy and handling verification data securely.\r\n\r\nDo_2 (Minimal Execution)\r\n\r\nPerform verification manually using documents submitted by the candidate.\r\n\r\nComplete checks post-offer but before providing system or data access.\r\n\r\nRecord results in the HR file or spreadsheet.\r\n\r\nCommunicate screening outcome to hiring manager for review.	Check_1 (Strong Review)\r\n\r\nConduct quarterly audits to ensure all employees in sensitive roles have completed screenings.\r\n\r\nVerify that third-party agencies follow contractual obligations and maintain confidentiality.\r\n\r\nReview screening reports for completeness, accuracy, and timeliness.\r\n\r\nTrack and analyze trends in screening results to identify risk patterns or recurring issues.\r\n\r\nReport any discrepancies or non-compliance cases to management and take corrective actions.\r\n\r\nEnsure alignment with evolving legal and regulatory screening requirements.\r\n\r\nCheck_2 (Minimal Review)\r\n\r\nVerify annually that all recent hires have completed background checks.\r\n\r\nReview screening documents during internal HR audits.\r\n\r\nConfirm that only authorized personnel have access to screening data.	Act_1 (Strong Improvement)\r\n\r\nUpdate screening policies and criteria based on:\r\n\r\nChanges in law or regulatory standards.\r\n\r\n