n.\r\n\r\nImplement segregation of duties between approvers and implementers of access rights.	Check_1 \r\n\r\nConduct monthly reviews of privileged accounts for necessity, validity, and assigned ownership.\r\n\r\nValidate that revoked users∩┐╜ privileged access is deactivated immediately.\r\n\r\nReview PAM audit logs for unauthorized privilege elevation or unusual activity.\r\n\r\nVerify compliance with access control policy and segregation of duties principles.\r\n\r\nCheck_2\r\n\r\nPerform quarterly certification of privileged accounts and temporary access rights.\r\n\r\nAnalyze PAM logs for failed access attempts or excessive privilege usage.\r\n\r\nReview configuration of MFA and session recording to ensure operational effectiveness.\r\n\r\nConfirm that all access changes are properly documented and approved.	Act_1 \r\n\r\n\r\nUpdate PAM policies and workflows based on audit and incident review findings.\r\n\r\nEnhance automation in provisioning and revocation using IAM/PAM integration.\r\n\r\nTrain administrators and approvers on secure handling of privileged credentials.\r\n\r\nAct_2\r\n\r\nPlan next-quarter initiative to implement AI-driven privilege behavior analytics for anomaly detection.\r\n\r\nExpand PAM integration across DevOps pipelines and CI/CD environments.\r\n\r\nAutomate risk-based access decisions and adaptive authentication for high-value assets.\r\n\r\nSchedule continuous improvement reviews for PAM effectiveness and policy compliance.		[]	\N	[]	2025-11-03 00:00:00+05:30	00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001	73736e58-df6d-4af5-bee6-ec2242ade0ef	\N	\N	CADP
