14	DPP-011	To be analyzed		Cybersecurity	guru.g@cavininfotech.com	Data Protection & Privacy	Implement Data Breach Notification Procedures	Establish procedures for breach notification to supervisory authorities within 72 hours and to individuals where required	A.5.34	RS.CO-2	P7.1	Art 33-34	Sec 72A	Req 12.10	164.408	Critical	Need clarity	2025-11-16 00:00:00+05:30	Need to check with murali	[]	Plan_1 \r\n\r\nDevelop and document a Data Breach Response and Notification Policy aligned with GDPR, CCPA, and other privacy laws.\r\n\r\nDefine roles and responsibilities for incident response (Infra, Security, Legal, and Privacy teams).\r\n\r\nEstablish a clear 72-hour notification timeline to report breaches to the relevant supervisory authority.\r\n\r\nDefine criteria to determine breach severity and when notification to affected individuals is required.\r\n\r\nCreate and maintain a Data Breach Register to record incidents, investigations, and actions taken.\r\n\r\nIntegrate Incident Response and Privacy Teams into a coordinated escalation process.\r\n\r\nDevelop breach communication templates for notifying authorities and impacted individuals.\r\n\r\nEstablish secure channels for internal breach reporting (e.g., ticketing system or hotline).\r\n\r\nConduct risk assessments on infrastructure systems to identify potential breach points.\r\n\r\nInclude breach notification requirements in vendor contracts and SLAs.\r\n\r\nPlan_2 \r\n\r\nMaintain a simple Incident Notification Procedure document.\r\n\r\nAssign a single point of contact (Privacy Officer or Infra Lead) for breach notifications.\r\n\r\nMaintain a basic log for all privacy-related incidents.\r\n\r\nDraft email templates for notifying authorities and individuals in case of a confirmed breach.\r\n\r\nConduct awareness sessions for Infra staff on timely reporting of data incidents.	Do_1 \r\n\r\nImplement a real-time incident detection system integrated with SIEM or monitoring tools.\r\n\r\nCreate an automated breach notification workflow to alert Privacy Officers and Legal within minutes of detection.\r\n\r\nEnsure encryption and access controls are in place for all systems handling PII.\r\n\r\nTest the incident escalation process quarterly to validate 72-hour reporting readiness.\r\n\r\nMaintain detailed documentation of the investigation, containment, and mitigation steps.\r\n\r\nCommunicate with third-party providers immediately upon breach identification to coordinate responses.\r\n\r\nConduct root cause analysis (RCA) after every major incident and update policies accordingly.\r\n\r\nSecurely retain all evidence and logs for audit and regulatory compliance.\r\n\r\nDo_2 \r\n\r\nUse email or a shared drive for manual breach reporting and tracking.\r\n\r\nEscalate incidents manually to Privacy and Legal contacts.\r\n\r\nStore all breach-related communication in a central folder for reference.\r\n\r\nSend notifications using predefined templates after management approval.\r\n\r\nConduct post-incident discussions to identify lessons learned.	Check_1 \r\n\r\nPerform quarterly reviews of breach logs to confirm all notifications were completed on time.\r\n\r\nValidate that 72-hour notification deadlines were met for all reportable breaches.\r\n\r\nReview audit trails and logs for accuracy and completeness of incident handling.\r\n\r\nConduct annual tabletop exercises simulating a data breach event.\r\n\r\nEvaluate communication effectiveness ∩┐╜ confirm that impacted individuals and regulators were properly informed.\r\n\r\nReview vendor compliance with breach notification clauses.\r\n\r\nCheck_2 \r\n\r\nReview breach register monthly or quarterly for completeness.\r\n\r\nVerify if timelines were met for authority notifications.\r\n\r\nConduct one annual review of the breach response documentation.\r\n\r\nEnsure all staff are aware of reporting procedures and contacts.	Act_1 \r\n\r\nAutomate the breach notification process through integrated alert systems.\r\n\r\nImplement centralized dashboards to track breach response performance and timelines.\r\n\r\nUpdate breach procedures based on new regulations or audit findings.\r\n\r\nConduct refresher training for Infra, Security, and Privacy teams after any major breach.\r\n\r\nInclude data breach scenarios in incident response drills.\r\n\r\nReview and strengthen vendor agreements to ensure timely cooperation during incidents.\r\n\r\nAct_2 \r\n\r\nUpdate breach templates and logs after each incident.\r\n\r\nRevise escalation lists based on personnel or organizational changes.\r\n\r\nAdd new systems or processes to the breach notification scope as they are deployed.\r\n\r\nConduct short awareness sessions to reinforce breach reporting importance.		[]	\N	[]	\N	00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001	96357816-1e75-4f96-8ea0-bb0f4e2be98b	\N	\N	CADP
