24	AIM-007	To check with Ganagavathy for this implementation	This is in place	\N	rama.n@cavininfotech.com	Access Control & Identity Management	Create Secure Password Policy	Establish strong password policy with complexity requirements, rotation, and protection mechanisms	A.8.5	PR.AC-1	CC6.1	Art 32	Sec 43A	Req 8.2	164.312(a)	High	Partially Implemented	2025-11-28 13:08:43.447251+05:30	To be finalised on thursday	[{"text": "tttt", "time": "11/28/2025, 1:08:42 PM", "author": "praveen.a@cavininfotech.com"}]	Plan_1 :\r\n1.Establish a central authentication policy requiring multi-factor authentication (MFA) for all privileged and remote access accounts.\r\n2?. Implement a centralized Identity and Access Management (IAM) system to manage, monitor, and audit all user logins.\r\n3?. Define strong password standards (length, complexity, expiry), session timeout rules, and login attempt limits for all systems.\r\n4?. Require encryption of authentication data both in transit and at rest to prevent credential compromise.\r\n\r\nPlan_2 :\r\n1?. Enforce basic password protection and enable MFA for high-risk or admin accounts.\r\n2?. Display system access warnings (∩┐╜Authorized users only∩┐╜) during login.\r\n3?. Apply simple timeout and account lockout settings for failed login attempts.	Do_1:\r\n1?. Configure MFA on all core applications, remote access tools, and admin accounts.\r\n2?. Disable plain-text password transmission; enforce secure login methods (HTTPS, VPN).\r\n3?. Educate employees to avoid password reuse or sharing and report suspicious login prompts.\r\n\r\nDo_2:\r\n1?. Deploy IAM or authentication tools (e.g., Okta, Azure AD, Google Workspace Admin).\r\n2?. Set up biometric or token-based authentication for sensitive systems.\r\n3?. Maintain documentation of all authentication methods and communicate to staff.	Check_1:\r\n1?.Conduct quarterly audits of login logs to detect repeated failures or unusual access.\r\n2?. Review whether MFA is enabled for all required users and systems.\r\n3?. Test login processes to ensure password complexity and timeout rules are active.\r\n\r\nCheck_2:\r\n1?. Review authentication-related incidents like phishing or unauthorized logins.\r\n2?. Analyze IAM reports for inactive, unused, or orphaned accounts.\r\n3?. Verify alerts are generated for failed login attempts and suspicious login behavior.	Act_1:\r\n1?. Fix audit findings ∩┐╜ enforce MFA where missing, close inactive accounts, and patch weak authentication settings.\r\n2?. Update authentication policies to include new methods (hardware tokens, adaptive MFA).\r\n3?. Re-train users after incidents to reinforce secure login practices.\r\n\r\nAct_2:\r\n1?. Continuously improve ∩┐╜ automate MFA enforcement and integrate IAM alerts into SIEM.\r\n2?. Add authentication performance metrics (failed logins, MFA success rates) to management reviews.\r\n3?. Use lessons learned from incidents to strengthen policies and access procedures.		[]	\N	[]	\N	00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001	171b16c4-bc1d-4bf7-a584-28a9cd0d72af	\N	Development	CADP
13	DPP-007	To be analyzed		\N	guru.g@cavininfotech.com	Data Protection & Privacy	Establish Data Subject Rights Management	Implement processes for handling data subject rights (access, rectification, erasure, portability, objection)	A.5.34	PR.DS-1	P4.1	Art 15-22	Sec 72	N/A	164.524	Critical	Need clarity	2025-11-13 00:00:00+05:30	Need to check with murali	[{"text": "Reviewed", "time": "12/11/2025, 16:03:24"}, {"text": "Test @bhuvanesh.b@hepl.com", "time": "13/11/2025, 15:40:49", "author": "saran.s@hepl.com"}]	Plan_1 \r\n\r\nDefine a Data Subject Rights (DSR) Policy in alignment with GDPR, CCPA, and other applicable privacy laws.\r\n\r\nEstablish a formal procedure for receiving, validating, and fulfilling data subject requests (DSRs).\r\n\r\nIdentify all data repositories containing personal data across on-premises and cloud infrastructure.\r\n\r\nImplement identity verification processes before granting access or making data changes.\r\n\r\nAssign clear roles and responsibilities for DSR handling (e.g., Privacy Officer, Data Protection Team, Infra Lead).\r\n\r\nIntegrate DSR workflows into Service Management or Ticketing Systems (e.g., ServiceNow, Jira).\r\n\r\nDocument response timelines for each type of request (e.g., 30 days for GDPR compliance).\r\n\r\nEstablish secure communication channels for fulfilling subject requests (encrypted email or secure portal).\r\n\r\nInclude privacy-by-design principles in infrastructure-level processes like backups, logs, and archiving.\r\n\r\nDevelop awareness training for IT and Infra teams on handling DSRs securely.\r\n\r\nPlan_2 \r\n\r\nMaintain a simple Data Subject Request (DSR) handling document.\r\n\r\nAssign a single point of contact (POC) for DSR coordination.\r\n\r\nIdentify core systems where PII is stored (e.g., HR systems, customer databases).\r\n\r\nRecord all received DSRs in a basic log or spreadsheet for tracking.\r\n\r\nUse standard templates for request acknowledgment and closure.	Do_1 \r\n\r\nDeploy an automated DSR management workflow integrated with infrastructure and data storage systems.\r\n\r\nImplement APIs or scripts for data retrieval, correction, and erasure across distributed systems.\r\n\r\nEnsure audit logging of all actions taken during DSR fulfillment for traceability.\r\n\r\nUse encryption and secure transfer protocols (TLS, SFTP) for sharing data with data subjects.\r\n\r\nCoordinate with third-party service providers to ensure timely response to data erasure or rectification requests.\r\n\r\nImplement access control and segregation of duties for Infra staff managing DSR activities.\r\n\r\nMaintain redundant logging to track DSR request timestamps, actions, and final status.\r\n\r\nDo_2 \r\n\r\nCreate manual workflows using shared drives or ticketing systems to manage DSRs.\r\n\r\nExport requested personal data manually upon user request.\r\n\r\nUse password-protected files or encrypted email to share requested data.\r\n\r\nMaintain a shared log for request completion dates and pending actions.\r\n\r\nValidate DSR completion via email acknowledgment from the requester.	Check_1 \r\n\r\nPerform quarterly reviews of DSR logs to ensure compliance with privacy regulations.\r\n\r\nVerify timely response and closure of all data subject requests (e.g., within 30 days).\r\n\r\nConduct privacy and security audits to confirm that erased data is unrecoverable from backups.\r\n\r\nReview identity verification procedures for adequacy and effectiveness.\r\n\r\nAssess vendor DSR compliance for systems hosted externally or on cloud platforms.\r\n\r\nTrack metrics (e.g., request volume, average resolution time, non-compliance incidents) for management reporting.\r\n\r\nCheck_2 \r\n\r\nReview DSR request log monthly or quarterly for completeness.\r\n\r\nConfirm that erasure or access requests are fulfilled as per documented timelines.\r\n\r\nVerify that encryption and secure sharing measures are applied during data transfer.\r\n\r\nConduct annual internal audit of DSR handling documentation.	Act_1 (Strong I\r\n\r\nAutomate DSR verification and response workflows across all Infra systems.\r\n\r\nIntegrate AI-based classification tools to identify PII across structured and unstructured data.\r\n\r\nImplement real-time dashboards for DSR performance and SLA monitoring.\r\n\r\nUpdate DSR procedures to include new data sources or changes in regulatory requirements.\r\n\r\nConduct refresher training for Infra and Privacy teams based on audit findings.\r\n\r\nCollaborate with Dev and Security teams to embed privacy automation in infrastructure-as-code (IaC) pipelines.\r\n\r\nAct_2 \r\n\r\nUpdate tracking templates or spreadsheets to capture more request details.\r\n\r\nRevise DSR procedures based on audit observations or compliance updates.\r\n\r\nAdd new systems or data repositories into the DSR process as they are onboarded.\r\n\r\nImprove communication templates for acknowledgment and closure notifications.		[{"text":"Test Observation","type":"Observation","time":"13/11/2025, 15:40:51","author":"saran.s@hepl.com"}]	\N	[]	\N	00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001	8bbe1cb6-8099-4276-80e0-e52926cdbb1a	praveen.a@cavininfotech.com	Security	CADP
